[1] Cases in various countries
Asia
---
Myanmar
- Karen State. 20 Jul 2018. Up to 436 people have been infected with dengue fever within the first 7 months of 2018 in the Karen (Kayin) State, the State Department of Public Health said. The dengue fever cases have been reported from 1 Jan to 14 Jul 2018, and the majority of the cases occurred in Hpa-an Township. There have been 306 cases in Hpa-an Township, 35 cases in Kawkareik Township, 39 cases in Hlaingbwe Township, 20 cases in Myawaddy Township, 8 cases in Kyainseikgyi Township, 22 cases in Hpapun Township, and 6 cases in Thandaung Township.
https://www.bnionline.net/en/news/karen-state-reports-436-cases-dengue-fever-within-seven-months

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Myanmar: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5947027,148]

Bangladesh
- National. 29 Jul 2018. About 1000 cases of dengue have been reported so far this year [2018] in Bangladesh, resulting in the deaths of 8 people in the capital Dhaka. Abdur Rahim, an official at the control room of the Directorate General of Health Services (DGHS) under the Ministry of Health, told Xinhua Sunday [29 Jul 2018] that "22 fresh cases of dengue were reported from Dhaka in the 24 hours as of 12:00 pm local time Saturday [28 Jul 2018], bringing the total number of confirmed cases till July 28 this year [2018] in the capital city to 992."
http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2018-07/29/c_137355773.htm

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Bangladesh: http://healthmap.org/r/1VpI]

Pakistan
- Punjab (Lahore). 29 Jul 2018. In 2018, as many as 15 437 dengue cases had been detected and eradicated so far, including 428 in Lahore city. According to statistics, 14 909 larvae were found in Kasur, Sheikhupura and Nankana Sahib, which were ignored by the concerned departments. According to details, the dengue surveillance teams have visited 831 000 places and lodged 78 cases in different police stations over not taking preventive measures, despite handing out warnings to them, from January 2018 up until now [29 Jul 2018].
https://dailytimes.com.pk/274794/dengue-on-the-rise-in-lahore/

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Punjab, Pakistan: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5947027,30911]

India
- Odisha (Bhubaneswar). 13 Jul 2018. Unable to check the mosquito menace in Odisha, dengue has spread to 12 districts in the state. Cuttack district has topped the list with 24 cases: 8 patients have been identified in Jajpur, 6 each in Balasore and Jagatsinghpur, 5 in Nayagarh, 4 in Khordha, 3 each in Kendrapara and Bhadrak, 2 in Puri and one each in Angul, Keonjhar and Sundargarh districts. Sources in the SCB Medical College and Hospital, Cuttack, said a sample test of 33 patients was conducted Thursday [12 Jul 2018] and 5 were found to be infected by the vector-borne disease. Of a total of 17 patients undergoing treatment at the special dengue ward of the SCB, 4 have been admitted to the ICU in a critical condition, the sources added. Of 24 dengue patients in Cuttack, 7 patients are from Tangi and 6 from the Jagatpur Industrial Estate area.
http://www.orissapost.com/12-districts-affected-by-dengue-in-odisha/

- Odisha (Bhubaneswar). 23 Jul 2018. Dengue cases in Odisha have increased and are spreading its tentacles to 29 districts, with Jharsuguda as an exception, till Monday [23 Jul 2018]. A total of 13 persons were tested at SCB Medical College and Hospital, Cuttack, and one among them was found to be infected with the vector-borne disease. The person belongs to Sambalpur district. In the past 45 days [early June to 23 Jul 2018], 134 patients have tested positive for dengue, which has so far claimed 2 lives this season. Cuttack district has reported the highest number with 62 dengue patients, informed SCB Medical authorities. A sample test of 2219 patients from Odisha, Andhra Pradesh, Chhatisgarh, West Bengal, Bihar, Maharashtra, Jharkhand and Madhya Pradesh was conducted in past 7 months [January to July 2018]. Of these, 189 were found positive for dengue. While 16 dengue cases were reported from Tangi, 9 were from Choudwar and 8 from Jagatpur. At present, 33 dengue patients are under treatment in the dengue ward of SCB and 6 among them have been admitted to the ICU.
http://www.orissapost.com/dengue-cases-on-rise-in-state/

- Chhattisgarh (Bhilai). 28 Jul 2018. Dengue cases are on the rise in eastern India. In the past 2 weeks [14-28 Jul 2018] 91 cases have been reported in Steel City.
http://thehitavada.com/Encyc/2018/7/28/Dengue-cases-rise-in-Bhilai.aspx

- New Delhi. 31 Jul 2018. Civic agencies report a total of 107 dengue cases, with 17 reported last week [23-30 Jul 2018].
https://www.dailypioneer.com/city/25-malaria-17-dengue--cases-reported-last-week.html

- Himachal Pradesh. 1 Aug 2018. A total of 544 cases have been reported as of 31 Jul 2018.
https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/nearly-550-dengue-cases-reported-in-himachal-118080101107_1.html

- Madhya Pradesh (Indore). 1 Aug 2018. The number of cases rises to 57.
http://www.freepressjournal.in/indore/indore-dengue-on-rise-three-more-test-positive/1325819

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of India: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5947027,142]

Philippines
- Leyte (Baybay). 17 Jul 2018. Authorities have declared a state of health emergency in this city due to the increasing number of dengue cases, a city health officer said Tuesday [17 Jul 2018]. Some 173 dengue cases, with 3 deaths, have been recorded in the city as of Tuesday [17 Jul 2018]. A total of 1947 cases, with 16 deaths, were recorded in Eastern Visayas.
http://news.abs-cbn.com/news/07/17/18/health-emergency-declared-in-baybay-leyte-due-to-dengue-uptick

- West Visyas. 18 Jul 2018. Dengue cases in Western Visayas this year [2018] reached 4009 cases with 29 deaths, data from the Department of Health (DOH) showed. The cases were recorded from 1 Jan to 7 Jul [2018], according to Dr. Rose Marie Lamirez, DOH Region 6 dengue medical program coordinator. These figures were 21% higher than the 3309 dengue cases with 27 deaths recorded in the same period last year [2017], said Lamirez.
https://www.panaynews.net/west-visayas-dengue-cases-breach-4t-mark/

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Philippines: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5947027,158]

Cambodia
- National. 3 Aug 2018. A sharp rise in cases have been reported, with 10 deaths reported from 5284 cases in first 6 months of 2018, a rise of 234 percent.
http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2018-08/03/c_137365842.htm

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Cambodia: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5947027,145]

China
- Macau. 27 Jul 2018. The 4th dengue case has been recorded this year [2018].
http://www.macaubusiness.com/macau-fourth-dengue-case-recorded-this-year-health-bureau/

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Macau: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5947027,363]

Viet Nam
- Ho Chi Minh City. 30 Jul 2018. A decrease of 36% of dengue cases in first 7 months of 2018 with one death has been reported.
https://en.vietnamplus.vn/ho-chi-minh-city-records-first-death-to-dengue-fever-in-2018/135560.vnp

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Vietnam: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5947027,152]

Taiwan
- New Taipei. 18 Jul 2018. Taiwan reports its first cluster case of dengue fever in New Taipei. According to CDC statistics, from the start of this year [2018] up until 17 Jul [2018], the country had recorded 3 indigenous cases of dengue fever comprising 2 cases in New Taipei and one in Kaohsiung. In addition, there have also been 109 imported cases of dengue fever for this year [2018], the statistics show.
http://focustaiwan.tw/news/asoc/201807180020.aspx

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Taiwan: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5947027,665]

Malaysia
- Kuala Lumpur and Putrajaya. 28 Jul 2018. A total of 3488 dengue cases with 6 deaths were recorded in Kuala Lumpur and Putrajaya from January [2018] until 21 Jul [2018]. An increase of an average of 195 cases weekly over the past 10 weeks has been reported. The highest case was recorded last week [20-27 Jul 2018] with 278 cases compared with 224 cases the previous week, an increase of 54 cases (24.1%).
https://www.malaymail.com/s/1656977/3488-dengue-cases-in-kl-putrajaya-so-far-this-year

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Malaysia: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5947027,147]

Lao PDR
- National. 20 Jul 2018. Dengue fever kills 12 in Lao PDR in first 6 months this year [2018]. According to local daily Vientiane Times on Friday [20 Jul 2018], the central Lao province of Savannakhet has recorded the most cases. The number of dengue fever cases was more than double the number of cases during the same period in 2017, higher than other ASEAN countries compared with the population, the report quoted a Lao health official as saying. In 2017, about 5584 dengue fever infections were recorded in the country including 14 fatalities. From 1 Jan to 30 Jun 2018, more than 2426 cases of dengue fever were recorded in Lao PDR. Of them, some 12 people died, National Center for Laboratory and Epidemiology director Onechanh Keosavanh told Vientiane Times on Thursday [19 Jul 2018].
https://en.trend.az/world/other/2931383.html

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Lao PDR: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5947027,146]

Yemen
- Maarib Province. 20 Jul 2018. At least 132 suspected cases of dengue fever have been reported in Yemen's eastern Maarib province in recent weeks, according to the Yemeni Health Ministry.
https://www.aa.com.tr/en/middle-east/yemen-officials-raise-alarm-over-dengue-fever-outbreak/1209209

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Yemen: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5947027,126]

[Yemen is endemic for dengue fever and has had several outbreaks since 2009 in many governorates. The past 2 years (2016-2018) have witnessed a sustained transmission of dengue fever/dengue hemorrhagic fever in most of the Red Sea coastal cities of Yemen. The current report is not surprising because there is a large dam at Maarib and much irrigation is undertaken (SB). The poor and collapsing heath infrastructure has also played and is still playing a significant role in this prolonged outbreak. - Mod.UBA]

Europe
---
Italy ex unknown. 20 Jul 2018. A case of dengue was diagnosed in a person residing in Guastalla who recently returned from a trip to an area where this disease is endemic.
https://www.ilrestodelcarlino.it/reggio-emilia/cronaca/dengue-guastalla-1.4048006

Australia
---
- New South Wales (Illawarra). 24 Jul 2018. A total of 7 Illawarra residents have been struck down by dengue fever while holidaying overseas this year [2018], prompting advice from the public health unit. Illawarra Shoalhaven Local Health District acting public health director Glendon Lee said the figures were consistent with previous years, but were a timely reminder to be travel safe. "In 2017 there were 15 dengue notifications in the ISLHD. When laboratories confirm dengue fever, they notify their local public health unit who follow up each case to determine where the person acquired the infection," he said.
https://www.illawarramercury.com.au/story/5544432/illawarra-dengue-fever-cases-prompt-public-health-warning/?cs=300

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of New South Wales, Australia: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5947027,284]

